I want to bring my happy FunSized self back to your feed. 😁
I am so incredibly grateful for the amount of support I am receiving. From all the comments on all of the different platforms, to the calls & texts, DMs & emails, thank you. Standing up for yourself & others is never an easy task but the fact that I am already starting to make a small change, makes it all worth it. 

Thank you, thank you, thank you! 🫶

But don’t worry, the FunSized Fight isn’t giving up any time soon!! 😉

Since posting my video on Friday, I have learned so much & I’ve had such interesting conversations with people. 
And that is part of what I wanted to accomplish. This is a part of the awareness that needs to be made. There needs to be more discussions around how usage is being described and broken down in castings. 
One of the biggest things I learned was what OOH advertising is, which is the MOST EXPENSIVE FORM of advertising. This billboard falls under OOH. So for the people who thought I was crying & playing the victim for a few hundred bucks & I should get over it, learning about OOH just adds to how deceitful the talent & ad agency were in including this in “all media” for a few hundred bucks. 
I also learned that this has been happening for years in Florida & no one has ever spoken up previously to try and make a change. 
Well, like I said in one of my reels, the New Yorker is in town now & I’m going to work hard to make sure this doesn’t continue to happen. 💪🏻
Thank you for your continuous support and for those of you who told me you were in similar situations and felt like you couldn’t speak up, I’m glad that I can try to be that voice for you, myself and anyone else who needs it. 🫶
